  "text": "Compatibility tests between pairs of plasmids were carried out by the method of [CITATION_1] . Segregation resulting from incompatibility usually yielded only 10-50% of colonies carrying both plasmids, whereas the rate of segregation of compatible plasmids was no higher than that of their spontaneous loss from strains carrying the plasmids separately. Residual hybrids carrying incompatible plasmids continued to segregate.",
